## `_work/` directory convention

All live agent working state lives under the `_work/` directory. This is project-specific content produced by agents during the build lifecycle.

| Path | Purpose | Who writes it |
|------|---------|---------------|
| `_work/spec/sc-0000-initial.yaml` | Baseline product spec (never modified by agents) | Dev (once, at project start) |
| `_work/spec/sc-[ID].yaml` | Per-story overlay (new/changed entries only) | Story Refiner |
| `_work/build/sc-[ID].yaml` | Build file: domain_context, ac_verifications, anti_patterns, gate results | Build Orchestrator (creates), Builder (extends) |
| `_work/stacks/` | Project-owned stack profiles (copied from templates) | Dev (initial), customized per project |
| `_work/ux/` | UX agent working files (prototype HTML, components YAML) | UX Designer |

### Build file schema

The build file (`_work/build/sc-[ID].yaml`) is written by the orchestrator at dispatch time and extended by the builder before writing code. All pipeline state lives here.

```yaml
story: sc-123
agent: service_builder
dispatched_at: "YYYY-MM-DD"
domain_context: {}        # relevant slice of spec
ac_verifications:         # copied from _work/spec/sc-[ID].yaml
  - id: AC-FUNC-01
    criterion: "description"
    verify: 'shell command'
anti_patterns: [...]      # from stack profile forbidden_patterns
test_patterns: [...]      # from stack profile test patterns
lessons: [...]            # from LESSONS.md if applicable
files:
  modified: []            # builder fills before coding
  created: []
  deleted: []
gates:
  tdd_red:     {status: pending, commit: "", test_count: 0, failing: 0}
  tdd_green:   {status: pending, commit: "", tampering: []}
  code_review: {status: pending}
  validation:  {status: pending}
```

## Agents

### Workflow agents (invoked directly via skills)

| Agent | Skill | What it does |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| Story Refiner / Refinement | `/refine` | Refines stories: adds ACs, creates spec overlay, sets priority |
| Build Orchestrator | `/build` | Finds refined stories, sorts by priority, dispatches to builder, runs quality gates |
| Story Reviewer | `/review` | Verifies ACs against committed code, posts PASS/FAIL verdict |
| UX Designer | `/ux` | Produces IA, user flows, design tokens, wireframe specs |
| Spec Generator | `/spec` | Merges YAML spec overlays into readable markdown |
| Validator | `/validate` | Independent AC verification using verify: commands |

### Builder agents (dispatched by the orchestrator)

| Agent | Scope | When used |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| Service Builder (builder-service) | Backend services: models, routers, schemas, tests | Most backend stories |
| Frontend Builder (builder-frontend) | Pages, components, hooks, API client, tests | Frontend stories |
| Infra Engineer (builder-infra) | Docker, CI/CD, proxy, config | Infrastructure stories |
| Migration Engineer (builder-migration) | Database migrations, schema alignment tests | Alembic/migration stories |
| Exchange Adapter (builder-exchange) | Exchange integrations, order logic (safety-critical) | CCXT/exchange stories |

### Quality gate agents (run automatically)

| Agent | Trigger | What it does |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| Test Engineer (test-engineer) | TDD RED phase (before builder) | Writes failing tests from spec before code exists |
| Code Reviewer | After every build commit | 3-pass review: KISS, lint/security, safety/correctness |
| Security Auditor | After backend/exchange builds | OWASP Top 10 checks; CRITICAL/HIGH blocks story |
| Validator | After code review passes | Independent AC verification; max 3 retry cycles |

